========================================================
Round Robin
========================================================
Preemptive. Each ready process gets at most quantum=3 time units per turn. Arrivals at a time-slice boundary are queued before the preempted process.

Execution timeline:
  [ 0,  3)  P1
  [ 3,  6)  P2
  [ 6,  9)  P3
  [ 9, 11)  P4
  [11, 14)  P1
  [14, 15)  P2
  [15, 16)  P3

Compact Gantt view:
  |0 P1 |3 P2 |6 P3 |9 P4 |11 P1 |14 P2 |15 P3 |16

Per-process results:
Process        Arr   Burst    Prio  Deadline  FirstStart    Finish   Waiting  Turnaround  Response   Missed
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
P1               0       6       3        30           0        14         8          14         0       no
P2               1       4       2        30           3        15        10          14         2       no
P3               2       4       1        30           6        16        10          14         4       no
P4               3       2       4        30           9        11         6           8         6       no

Summary metrics:
  Makespan              : 16
  Total busy time       : 16
  CPU utilization       : 100.00%
  Throughput            : 0.25 processes/unit-time
  Average waiting time  : 8.50
  Average turnaround    : 12.50
  Average response time : 3.00
  Deadline misses       : 0 / 4


==================== POLICY COMPARISON ====================
Policy                              Avg Wait  Avg Turnaround      Avg Resp    Misses      Util %
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
FCFS - First Come First Served          6.00           10.00          6.00         0      100.00
SJF - Shortest Job First                5.00            9.00          5.00         0      100.00
Priority Scheduling                     6.00           10.00          6.00         0      100.00
Round Robin                             8.50           12.50          3.00         0      100.00

Interpretation hints:
  - Lower waiting/turnaround time is usually better for batch-style workloads.
  - Lower response time is important for interactive workloads.
  - Round Robin often improves response time, but can increase turnaround time.
  - Deadline misses show whether a policy is suitable for time-bound workloads.
